## Overview

The **Imperials** (also called Cyrodilics) are the human race native to **Cyrodiil** — the geographic and political heart of Tamriel. They are neither the strongest warriors nor the greatest mages, but they excel in what builds empires: **diplomacy**, **commerce**, **law**, and **administration**.

Three successive empires stand as testament to their organizational genius.

## Subgroups

The Imperials divide into two sub-cultures:

### The Colovians (West)
- Pragmatic warriors and farmers
- Austere and martial culture
- Closer to the Nords in temperament
- Cities: Skingrad, Chorrol, Kvatch
- Provide the majority of the legionnaires

### The Nibenese (East)
- Merchants, bureaucrats, and mages
- Refined and cosmopolitan culture
- River trade along the Niben
- Cities: Bravil, Leyawiin, Cheydinhal
- Provide the majority of administrators and diplomats

## The Three Empires

### The Alessian Empire (1E 243–2200+)
- Founded by **Alessia** after the revolt against the Ayleids
- First human empire in Tamriel
- Theocracy (Alessian Order)
- Fell into religious fanaticism

### The Reman Empire (1E 2703 – 2E 430)
- Founded by **Reman Cyrodiil**
- Integration of the Akaviri (who became the Blades)
- Conquest of nearly all of Tamriel (except Morrowind)
- Fell with the assassination of Reman III

### The Septim Empire (2E 854 – 4E 0)
- Founded by **Tiber Septim**
- The most vast and enduring
- Conquest of ALL of Tamriel (including Morrowind)
- Fell with the assassination of Uriel Septim VII and Martin

### The Mede Empire (4E 17 – ?)
- Founded by **Titus Mede** (a usurper)
- Weakened empire, shorn of provinces
- Signatory of the White-Gold Concordat
- Current status: in decline

## Culture

### Law and Order
- **Imperial Law** is the foundation of civilization for the Imperials
- The Imperial legal system is the most developed in Tamriel
- Contracts, treaties, and agreements are sacred
- "The pen is mightier than the sword" — the Imperial creed

### Commerce
- Imperials are born merchants
- The **Septim** (gold coin) is the universal currency of Tamriel
- Commercial guilds are headquartered in Cyrodiil
- "Voice of the Emperor" — racial power of persuasion

### Religion
The Imperial pantheon of **Eight (or Nine) Divines**:
- Akatosh, Arkay, Dibella, Julianos, Kynareth, Mara, Stendarr, Zenithar
- Talos (the Ninth, controversial since the Concordat)
- Imperial religion is syncretic — assembled from Elvish and human traditions

## The Imperial Legion

The Imperial army is the most **organized** military force:
- Strict hierarchy (General → Legate → Centurion → Legionnaire)
- Group tactics, formations, discipline
- Not the best individual fighters but unbeatable as an army
- Forts and camps across all of Tamriel
- Integrates all races (diversity as strength)

## Racial Traits

- Mediterranean/Roman appearance
- No notable elemental resistance
- **Voice of the Emperor** — ability to calm hostiles (charm)
- Commercial bonus (better prices)
- Standard human lifespan
- Versatility — good at everything, physically exceptional at nothing

## Perception by Others

| Race | Perception |
|------|-----------|
| Nords | "Weak but cunning, sold out to the Elves" |
| Redguards | "Good allies when it suits them" |
| Altmer | "Ephemeral and ambitious, useful as subjects" |
| Dunmer | "Colonizers with fine words" |
| Khajiit | "Good trade, laws too strict" |
| Orcs | "At least they give us a place" |

## Strengths and Weaknesses

### Strengths
- Unparalleled organization and administration
- Diplomacy and commerce
- Imperial Legion (organized army)
- Capacity to unite diverse peoples
- Political pragmatism

### Weaknesses
- No exceptional martial or magical trait
- Tendency toward imperialist arrogance
- Dependence on structures (collapse without the Empire)
- Chronic bureaucratic corruption
